{
  "id": "infiniflow_ragflow_14930",
  "repo_name": "infiniflow/ragflow",
  "repo_url": "https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow",
  "base_commit": "6794ad2f70f0b738c9456be278b69582c9687cf9",
  "pr_number": 14930,
  "issue_number": 14804,
  "issue_title": "[Feature Request]: Add Go driver for CometAPI model provider",
  "issue_body": "### Self Checks\n\n- [x] I have searched for existing issues [search for existing issues](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues), including closed ones.\n- [x] I confirm that I am using English to submit this report ([Language Policy](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues/5910)).\n- [x] Non-english title submitions will be closed directly ( \u975e\u82f1\u6587\u6807\u9898\u7684\u63d0\u4ea4\u5c06\u4f1a\u88ab\u76f4\u63a5\u5173\u95ed ) ([Language Policy](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues/5910)).\n- [x] Please do not modify this template :) and fill in all the required fields.\n\n### Is your feature request related to a problem?\n\n```Markdown\nYes. The Go rewrite of the RAGFlow model provider layer is tracked in #14736, and CometAPI is listed there as an unchecked provider. The Go layer does not yet route the \"cometapi\" provider name, so a tenant who configures CometAPI falls through to the dummy driver instead of calling the real CometAPI endpoints.\n\nCometAPI exposes OpenAI-compatible chat and embeddings endpoints, plus a public model catalog and a separate quota query API. Adding a Go driver will let RAGFlow tenants use CometAPI from the Go API server for common chat and embedding workflows.\n```\n\n### Describe the feature you'd like\n\nAdd a Go driver for CometAPI so that a tenant can configure CometAPI as a model provider in the Go layer and use chat, streaming chat, embeddings, model listing, connection checks, and balance queries end to end.\n\nConcretely:\n\n- New file internal/entity/models/cometapi.go with a CometAPIModel that implements the ModelDriver interface.\n- New tests in internal/entity/models/cometapi_test.go.\n- internal/entity/models/factory.go: route the \"cometapi\" provider name to NewCometAPIModel.\n- New conf/models/cometapi.json with CometAPI base URLs and representative chat / embedding models.\n\nInitial method coverage:\n\n- ChatWithMessages: POST https://api.cometapi.com/v1/chat/completions.\n- ChatStreamlyWithSender: same endpoint with stream:true and SSE parsing.\n- Embed: POST https://api.cometapi.com/v1/embeddings.\n- ListModels: GET https://api.cometapi.com/api/models.\n- CheckConnection: lightweight model-list or minimal API probe to verify the key / network path.\n- Balance: GET https://query.cometapi.com/user/quota?key=... using CometAPI's query service.\n- Rerank: return \"no such method\" unless a documented CometAPI rerank endpoint is confirmed.\n- TranscribeAudio / AudioSpeech / OCRFile: return \"no such method\" unless docs clearly confirm support and response shape.\n\nNo new public RAGFlow API. No ModelDriver interface change. The driver only adds a new provider implementation and a factory switch case.\n\n### Describe implementation you've considered\n\nFollow the existing OpenAI-compatible provider patterns in the Go layer, especially OpenAI / OpenRouter / Mistral, while handling CometAPI-specific endpoints separately:\n\n- base model API: https://api.cometapi.com/v1\n- public model catalog: https://api.cometapi.com/api/models\n- quota query service: https://query.cometapi.com/user/quota\n\n### Documentation, adoption, use case\n\n```Markdown\nNo new user-facing docs are required for the initial driver. CometAPI will appear in the model provider list once conf/models/cometapi.json ships.\n\nUse case: a tenant builds a knowledge base in RAGFlow and picks a CometAPI-backed chat or embedding model. With this change, the Go layer calls CometAPI's real endpoints with the tenant's API key instead of returning the dummy driver error.\n```\n\n### Additional information\n\nTracking issue: #14736\nCometAPI docs: https://apidoc.cometapi.com/\n\n",
